& [SourceSet] is the bounded source frame
  + [source_001] is Burns, Sakamoto, and Sano, On the theory of higher rank Euler, Kolyvagin and Stark systems, II
    = link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.08448
    = use: higher-rank Euler systems map to higher-rank Kolyvagin systems and can control Selmer module structures under hypotheses
  + [source_002] is Burns and Sano, On the theory of higher rank Euler, Kolyvagin and Stark systems
    = link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1612.06187
    = use: general construction and relation among higher-rank Euler, Kolyvagin, and Stark systems for p-adic representations
  + [source_003] is Karl Rubin, Higher rank Kolyvagin systems
    = link: https://www.math.uci.edu/~krubin/lectures/lausanne.pdf
    = use: Kolyvagin systems are designed to relate Selmer group structure to L-value or Euler-system data
  + [source_004] is Burns-Rubin workshop notes on higher rank Euler/Kolyvagin systems
    = link: https://math.berkeley.edu/~fengt/3Burns_Rubinfest.pdf
    = use: higher-rank Euler systems need denominator/lattice control and are not naive repetitions of rank-one systems

& [ResearchFindings] is the extracted theorem boundary
  + [finding_001] is higher-rank Kolyvagin machinery targets Selmer control
    = meaning: this route is strongest for upper_bound_control and Selmer-module structure, not direct source_count
  + [finding_002] is higher-rank Euler-to-Kolyvagin derivative maps exist in broad algebraic settings under hypotheses
    = meaning: the machinery can transform compatible global classes into control systems when the required system exists
  + [finding_003] is known examples of suitable Euler systems remain scarce
    = meaning: the mechanism does not automatically supply the source family needed for arbitrary elliptic curves and ranks
  + [finding_004] is denominator and Rubin-lattice issues are structural, not cosmetic
    = meaning: higher rank cannot be treated as repeated rank-one Heegner-point descent
  + [finding_005] is the route may avoid some direct height nondegeneracy pressure but introduces existence and compatibility pressure for higher-rank systems
    = meaning: the lock moves from nondegenerate pairing to constructing a suitable system and proving it controls exactly the desired Selmer rank

